name: HighlightData
description: Represents the highlight data added to the shape.

properties.name: width
properties.description: A positive integer that specifies the width of the highlight's stroke in pixels.

properties.name: color
properties.description: A string that specifies the color of the highlight. It must have the form "#RRGGBB", where each letter represents a hexadecimal digit between 0 and F, and where RR is the red value between 0 and 0xFF (255), GG the green value between 0 and 0xFF (255), and BB is the blue value between 0 and 0xFF (255).

methods.name: load
methods.description: Fills the proxy object created in JavaScript layer with property and object values specified in the parameter.

parameters.name: param
parameters.description: Accepts parameter and relationship names as delimited string or an array. Or, provide [loadOption](loadoption.md) object.
